Sentence: Although the data acquisition and the procedure for the subtraction of the magnetic background is identical for the two samples, the FeSe superconducting M(H) curve appears noisier than the curve of FeSeAg.
In fact, the critical current density of the Ag-doped sample is about two times the value of the corresponding undoped FeSe 0.94 material for low magnetic fields (up to 2.5 Tesla).
